# 🌍 Introduction

Color detection is one of the most important technologies used in modern embedded systems.

Today, color sensors can be found almost everywhere:

- 🏭 Industrial automation
- 🤖 Robotics
- 📦 Product sorting systems
- 🚗 Autonomous vehicles
- 🧪 Laboratory instruments
- 📷 Camera calibration
- 🎨 Color quality inspection
- 🍎 Food processing

Instead of relying on human vision, electronic systems use specialized sensors capable of measuring light with remarkable precision.

One of the most popular sensors for Arduino beginners is the **TCS3200 Color Sensor**.

Unlike many analog sensors, the TCS3200 does **not** output a voltage.

Instead, it converts light intensity into a digital square wave whose **frequency** changes according to the detected color.

This makes the sensor very resistant to electrical noise and allows microcontrollers to measure color using precise timing techniques.

---

# 🎯 Project Objectives

The purpose of this project is much more than simply reading RGB values.

By completing this project you will understand:

✅ Digital Electronics

✅ Frequency Measurement

