# 🔹 Understanding `#define`

One of the first things beginners notice is this:

```cpp
#define s0 8
```

Many people believe this creates a variable.

It does **not**.

`#define` is handled by the **C Preprocessor** before compilation begins.

Suppose your code contains

```cpp
