# 🧠 pinMode()

One of the most important Arduino functions.

```cpp
pinMode(s0, OUTPUT);
```

Conceptually it means

```
Arduino

↓

Configure Pin

↓

Output Mode
```

Internally something much more interesting happens.

The ATmega328P microcontroller contains registers called

```
DDRB

DDRC

DDRD
```

These registers determine whether each pin behaves as

```
Input

or

Output
```

When you call

```cpp
