# 📦 Understanding `pulseIn()`

The Arduino function

```cpp
pulseIn(sensorPin, LOW);
```

waits until the selected pin becomes LOW.

Then,

1. Start timer
2. Continue counting
3. Wait until signal changes
4. Stop timer
5. Return elapsed time

Pseudo-code:

```cpp
waitUntilLOW();

start = micros();

while(pin == LOW)
{
}

finish = micros();

return finish - start;
```

The returned value is measured in

```
Microseconds (μs)
```

