# HC-05 Bluetooth Module

## Overview

The HC-05 is a Bluetooth Classic (Bluetooth v2.0 + EDR) serial communication module designed to provide transparent UART communication between microcontrollers and Bluetooth-enabled devices.

Unlike many inexpensive Bluetooth modules, HC-05 supports both:

- Master Mode
- Slave Mode

This flexibility makes it highly suitable for peer-to-peer embedded communication.

---

## Internal Architecture

The HC-05 consists primarily of

- Bluetooth Radio
- UART Interface
- Flash Memory
- AT Command Processor
- Baseband Controller

Communication occurs through the UART interface while Bluetooth protocol management remains transparent to the Arduino.

