# Introduction

The rapid expansion of the Internet of Things (IoT) has significantly increased the demand for low-cost, internet-enabled embedded devices. Among the many wireless microcontrollers available today, the **ESP8266** has become one of the most influential technologies in modern electronics.

Released by Espressif Systems in 2014, the ESP8266 revolutionized embedded development by integrating a complete Wi-Fi subsystem and a programmable microcontroller into a single, inexpensive chip. This innovation dramatically lowered the barrier to entry for IoT projects, making wireless communication accessible to students, hobbyists, researchers, and industry professionals alike.

A popular development board built around this chip is the **NodeMCU**, which simplifies programming and hardware interfacing by adding USB connectivity, voltage regulation, and user-friendly pin headers.

