# What is ESP8266?

The **ESP8266** is a low-cost, highly integrated **32-bit Wi-Fi-enabled microcontroller** developed by **Espressif Systems**.

Unlike traditional Arduino boards, which require an external Wi-Fi module, the ESP8266 incorporates:

- A programmable CPU
- IEEE 802.11 b/g/n Wi-Fi
- TCP/IP networking stack
- Flash memory interface
- GPIO controller
- Analog-to-Digital Converter (ADC)
- Multiple communication peripherals

This integration allows a single chip to perform sensing, processing, and wireless communication simultaneously.

