# Programming NodeMCU

Programming NodeMCU follows the same process as programming the ESP8266.

Typical workflow:

1. Install the ESP8266 board package in Arduino IDE.
2. Select the appropriate NodeMCU board.
3. Connect the board via USB.
4. Compile and upload the sketch.

The integrated USB-to-UART converter handles firmware uploading automatically.

---

# Arduino IDE Integration

To program ESP8266 or NodeMCU using Arduino IDE:

1. Open **Preferences**.
2. Add the ESP8266 Board Manager URL.
3. Install the ESP8266 package via Board Manager.
4. Select **NodeMCU 1.0 (ESP-12E Module)** or the appropriate ESP8266 board.
5. Choose the correct COM port.
6. Upload the sketch.

This workflow enables developers familiar with Arduino to transition easily to Wi-Fi-enabled embedded systems.

