# 📖 About the Project

This project transforms an **Arduino Mega** into a simple capacitive touch piano.

Instead of using mechanical buttons, the piano detects the electrical capacitance of your finger. Once a touch is detected, the Arduino immediately generates the corresponding musical note through a buzzer.

The project demonstrates how capacitive sensing can be used to build interactive electronic musical instruments with minimal hardware.

