# 🧠 How It Works

```text
Finger Touch
      │
      ▼
Capacitive Sensor
      │
      ▼
Arduino Reads Sensor Value
      │
      ▼
Threshold Comparison
      │
      ▼
Play Musical Frequency
      │
      ▼
Buzzer Produces Sound
```

Each sensor continuously measures capacitance.

When the measured value exceeds the predefined threshold (`800`), the Arduino identifies the touched key and immediately generates its musical frequency using the built-in `tone()` function.

When no key is touched, `noTone()` stops the sound.

